item.description:
Lets say you have a User model with Lombok modelwide @Getter and @Setter:
@Getter @Setter public class User { @Id private String id; private String username; private String email; private String password; } setId(String id) makes no sense. Normally the id is set by the DB, so it makes no sense to set it.
So you can use @Setter(AccessLevel.NONE) (or @Getter(AccessLevel.NONE)) to exclude it from the Lombok setters (or getters)
